<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    ServiceNow Update Set record-definition for the `sys_dictionary` row that
    declares the `assigned_group` Reference field on the `x_[scope]_case`
    custom table inside the scoped application `x_[scope]_case_management`.

    Per AAP Section 0.5.7 (Data-Model Mapping verbatim):
        Field           Type                          Constraints
        assigned_group  Reference -> sys_user_group   Mandatory on Open transition

    THIS FIELD IS A PILLAR OF THE STATE-MACHINE GATE for Draft -> Open and
    of the role-based authorization model. Per AAP Section 0.5.5 the
    transition matrix's first non-trivial gate is:

        From   To    Required condition           Blocking-error behavior
        Draft  Open  assigned_group populated     Surface form-level error

    The "Mandatory on Open transition" qualifier is a TRANSITION-LEVEL
    constraint, NOT a FIELD-LEVEL constraint. A Draft case MUST be
    permitted to exist without an assigned_group - this is what enables
    the unauthenticated portal submission endpoint
    (../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_[scope]_case_submit.xml) to land
    new portal-submitted cases in Draft status without requiring the
    anonymous external requester to know about, much less choose, an
    internal ServiceNow group. The dictionary entry therefore declares
    `<mandatory>false</mandatory>`, and the Draft -> Open gate is enforced
    by the Flow Designer subflow at
    ../flows/sub_flows/validate_open_transition.xml. Setting
    `<mandatory>true</mandatory>` here would block save of Draft cases
    without a group, which directly contradicts AAP Section 0.5.7's
    enumerated state list (Draft is the FIRST allowed status) and AAP
    Section 0.5.1's portal-submission contract ("the submission page
    writes a new x_[scope]_case record with status = Draft and returns
    the auto-numbered number").

    Beyond the Draft -> Open gate, this field participates in three
    other critical mechanisms (AAP Sections 0.4.1, 0.5.6):

      1. AGENT MEMBERSHIP VALIDATION
         (../business_rules/x_[scope]_validate_assigned_agent_membership.xml)
         Per AAP Section 0.5.7: "assigned_agent | Reference -> sys_user |
         Optional; must be member of assigned_group". When a manager or
         agent populates assigned_agent, a before-update business rule
         verifies the chosen sys_user is a direct or indirect member of
         the chosen assigned_group via the OOB sys_user_grmember table.
         Failure surfaces a blocking error before save commits.

      2. FIELD-LEVEL ACL (write restricted to case_manager)
         (../acl/x_[scope]_case_assigned_group_field_acl.xml)
         Per AAP Section 0.5.6: "ACLs MUST be defined at table level AND
         field level for sensitive fields (assigned_group, assigned_agent)."
         The field-level ACL restricts write access to ONLY the
         x_[scope]_case_manager role - case_agent users can NEITHER
         re-assign their cases to a different group NOR set the group
         on a Draft case they did not create. The dictionary entry's
         own `<write_roles/>` element below is intentionally empty so
         that the dedicated ACL system (not the dictionary's role lists)
         governs write access. This is the standard ServiceNow pattern
         for fine-grained field protection.

      3. "ASSIGNED ONLY" READ/WRITE ACL CONDITION FOR case_agent
         (../acl/x_[scope]_case_read_agent_assigned.xml,
          ../acl/x_[scope]_case_write_agent_assigned.xml)
         Per AAP Section 0.5.6: "'Assigned only' = cases where
         assigned_agent = current user OR assigned_group contains current
         user." The table-level read/write ACLs for case_agent encode
         this condition as a scripted ACL expression that calls
         current.assigned_group.sys_id against the current user's
         sys_user_grmember rows. This field is therefore one of the TWO
         gates (alongside assigned_agent) that determine the visible
         case set for any agent.

    Semantic source-side reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported):
      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java line 255-256:
            @Column(name = "cm_responsible_organization")
            private String responsibleOrganization;
        ArkCase's `responsibleOrganization` was a free-form JPA String
        column on the `acm_case_file` entity, mapped to physical column
        `cm_responsible_organization`. Any caller could write any string
        - a department name, a team identifier, a vendor name, or simply
        the word "TBD" - with no platform-level validation that the
        named organization actually existed or that the calling user
        had any relationship to it. The ServiceNow target replaces this
        with a proper foreign key to the OOB `sys_user_group` table,
        gaining four critical capabilities:
          * Referential integrity: only existing, active groups may be
            chosen (the platform's reference picker enforces this; the
            scripted REST submission endpoint may bypass at insert time
            only because Draft cases legitimately have no group yet).
          * Membership semantics: the OOB `sys_user_grmember` join table
            provides direct user-group membership lookups via
            `gs.getUser().isMemberOf(groupSysId)`, which is what the
            "Assigned only" ACL condition and the agent-membership
            business rule both rely on.
          * Single source of truth: the same `sys_user_group` table that
            ServiceNow uses for all OOB role propagation, queue
            assignment, notification routing, and dashboard scoping is
            now the canonical "team" backing case responsibility.
          * Cascade safety: the platform's reference-deletion semantics
            (cascade rule, controlled by the `<reference_cascade_rule/>`
            element below - left empty for default "no cascade" behavior)
            prevent accidental orphaning of cases when a group is deleted.
        The ArkCase design's looseness was a known pain point referenced
        indirectly by the queue/state pipeline (CaseFileQueueHandler
        line 1-N which had to manually resolve queue from the free-form
        organization string) - the ServiceNow target eliminates that
        translation step entirely.
      - The field name is `assigned_group` (lowercase, snake_case; NOT
        `assignedGroup`, NOT `assigned_to_group`, NOT `responsible_group`)
        per AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim. This is an INTENTIONAL rename
        from ArkCase's `responsibleOrganization` to align with the
        ServiceNow convention used by OOB tables (incident.assignment_group,
        sc_request.assignment_group, change_request.assignment_group all
        use the `assignment_group` element name; AAP Section 0.5.7
        chose `assigned_group` as a near-identical variant for the
        scoped application).

    Constraints honored (AAP Sections 0.7.1, 0.7.2):
      - Scope-namespace exclusivity: `<name>` resolves to `x_[scope]_case`
        within the scoped application, and `<sys_scope>` / `<sys_package>`
        bind THIS dictionary record to the same scope by `source` attribute
        lookup. The `<reference>` element resolves to OOB `sys_user_group`
        by table name (NOT by sys_id), preserving zero-hardcoded-sys_id
        compliance. NO global-scope writes - the OOB `sys_user_group`
        table is REFERENCED but never modified.
      - Zero hardcoded cross-reference sys_ids: the `<sys_scope>`,
        `<sys_package>`, and `<reference>` text-node values resolve by
        scope source name and table name respectively, not by literal
        sys_id. The `<sys_id>` text-node value is THIS record's own
        deterministic primary key (MD5 of the canonical field identifier
        `x_[scope]_case.assigned_group`) and is NOT a reference to any
        other record. Per AAP Section 0.7.2 this scheme guarantees that
        a fresh PDI re-import of the Update Set produces byte-identical
        sys_id values, which is necessary for round-trip-verify
        (../scripts/round_trip_verify.md) zero-error preview.
      - The literal `[scope]` placeholder is preserved per AAP convention;
        the PDI auto-assigns the actual scope id at App Engine Studio
        creation time and substitutes it into every occurrence at export.
      - mandatory=false at the dictionary level (CRITICAL: AAP Section
        0.5.7's "Mandatory on Open transition" is a TRANSITION-LEVEL
        constraint enforced by the Flow Designer subflow at
        ../flows/sub_flows/validate_open_transition.xml, NOT a
        FIELD-LEVEL constraint enforced by the dictionary). Setting this
        to true would prevent Draft cases from being saved without an
        assigned_group, breaking AAP Section 0.5.7's enumerated state
        list (Draft is the first allowed status with no preconditions)
        and AAP Section 0.5.1's portal-submission contract (anonymous
        external requesters submit cases that land in Draft with no
        group set; an authenticated internal user later picks up the
        Draft and assigns a group as part of the Draft -> Open
        transition).
      - read_only=false: case_manager users edit this field directly to
        assign the responsible group. The field-level ACL in
        ../acl/x_[scope]_case_assigned_group_field_acl.xml enforces that
        ONLY case_manager may write; the dictionary-level read_only flag
        remains false so the field is editable in principle by qualifying
        roles.
      - default_value (empty): no automatic group assignment. The
        portal-submitted Draft case has no group; the case_manager
        explicitly chooses a group when promoting Draft -> Open.
      - audit=false: per AAP Section 0.3.1 minimal-change clause and
        consistent with the sibling DateTime / Choice / String fields
        in this same dictionary set, only the `status` field carries
        audit=true (it is the most important field for state-machine
        forensics). Group reassignment is logged through the standard
        sys_history_set / sys_audit infrastructure on demand but does
        not trigger the per-field audit overhead by default.
      - max_length=32: the standard ServiceNow Reference-field width.
        The dictionary stores the 32-character lowercase-hex sys_id of
        the referenced sys_user_group row as the actual column value;
        the platform's auto-generated form picker, list view, and report
        builder all dereference to the group's display column (name)
        for human-readable display via the OOB sys_user_group dictionary's
        `display=true` column.
      - choice=0: this is a Reference field, NOT a Choice field. The
        sibling sys_choice_* records under ../choices/ apply only to
        the `type`, `status`, `priority`, `pending_reason`,
        `case_task.type`, `case_task.status`, and `case_party.party_type`
        columns - none are needed here.
      - choice_field, choice_table empty: same reason as choice=0 above.
      - reference=sys_user_group: OOB ServiceNow group table. AAP
        Section 0.5.7 specifies this exact target table by name. No
        scoped wrapper or facade is needed; cases reference groups
        directly across the scoped/global boundary, which ServiceNow
        permits for OOB tables (the reverse direction - global tables
        referencing scoped tables - would require a Cross-Scope Privilege
        record, but is not needed for this POC).
      - reference_cascade_rule (empty): default platform behavior, which
        is "do nothing on referenced-record deletion." If a group is
        deleted, cases retain the orphaned reference; this is acceptable
        for the POC since group deletion is a manager-level operation
        already gated by global ACLs and is rare in practice. AAP does
        not specify a cascade rule.
      - reference_qual, reference_qual_condition (empty): no filter on
        which groups may be selected. Any active sys_user_group is
        eligible. AAP does not require filtering by group name pattern,
        type, or any other criterion.
      - use_reference_qualifier=simple: standard ServiceNow setting
        when no advanced (scripted) reference qualifier is in use.
      - dynamic_ref_qual (empty): no dynamic reference qualifier.
      - reference_floor, reference_key, reference_type (empty): standard
        defaults for a basic table-to-table reference; no advanced
        reference semantics (typeahead override, reference floor table,
        document reference, etc.) are needed here.
      - element_reference=false: this is a TABLE reference, not an
        ELEMENT reference (which would point at a specific dictionary
        column on another table). AAP specifies a row-level reference
        target.
      - table_reference=false: this is NOT a "Document ID" / "Table"
        polymorphic reference (which is what `glide_var` style fields
        on the OOB task table use to reference any-table-any-row). It
        is a fixed-target reference to sys_user_group only.
      - text_index=false: Reference fields are not full-text-indexed.
        Searches by group are performed via GlideRecord
        addJoinQuery against sys_user_group on its sys_id column;
        full-text indexing of the 32-char sys_id has no value.
      - unique=false: a single group is correctly responsible for many
        cases (that is the entire point of group-based case routing),
        so uniqueness on this column would be semantically wrong.
      - virtual=false: this is a stored column, not a calculated /
        virtual derivation. The actual sys_id of the chosen
        sys_user_group row is persisted on every record.
      - No PII: the field stores a 32-char sys_id pointer to a group
        record; the group itself stores categorical organizational
        labels (department names, team names) chosen at PDI bootstrap
        time and is not derived from any real person or customer. The
        seed group at ../seed-data/groups/sys_user_group_x_[scope]_demo_team.xml
        is fabricated synthetic data per AAP Section 0.7.2 ("synthetic
        only").

    Cross-references (AAP Section 0.5.2 dependency ordering):
      - This record MUST load AFTER:
          * ../tables/x_[scope]_case.xml (parent table; `<name>` here
            references the scoped table by name)
          * sys_user_group (OOB; always present on every PDI; never
            modified by this Update Set per AAP Section 0.3.2)
      - This record MUST load BEFORE the consumers that read or write
        the `assigned_group` column:
          * ../business_rules/x_[scope]_validate_assigned_agent_membership.xml
            (uses this field for membership validation: when
            assigned_agent is set, the rule queries sys_user_grmember
            for (current.assigned_agent, current.assigned_group) and
            blocks save with a form-level error if the agent is NOT a
            member of the group)
          * ../flows/sub_flows/validate_open_transition.xml (the
            Draft -> Open gate; the subflow inspects current.assigned_group
            and throws a blocking error if empty)
          * ../flows/general_inquiry_state_machine.xml (the parent flow
            for type=General Inquiry that calls validate_open_transition)
          * ../flows/complaint_state_machine.xml (the parent flow for
            type=Complaint that calls validate_open_transition)
          * ../script_includes/x_[scope]_CaseTransitionValidator.xml
            (canTransitionToOpen static method that reads current.assigned_group
            and is called by both the flows and the business rules)
          * ../acl/x_[scope]_case_assigned_group_field_acl.xml
            (field-level ACL: write restricted to case_manager)
          * ../acl/x_[scope]_case_read_agent_assigned.xml
            (table-level read ACL for case_agent; condition uses
            current.assigned_group to evaluate "Assigned only")
          * ../acl/x_[scope]_case_write_agent_assigned.xml
            (table-level write ACL for case_agent; same condition as
            the read ACL above)
          * ../seed-data/groups/sys_user_group_x_[scope]_demo_team.xml
            (the synthetic demo group that the demo cases will reference;
            this dictionary entry must precede the seed group for the
            preview engine to reconcile the field schema before the
            seed group's role assignments)
          * ../seed-data/cases/x_[scope]_case_demo_*.xml (synthetic demo
            cases that populate this field by lookup of the demo group's
            `name` attribute via the seed_demo_data.js script - never
            via hard-coded sys_id, per AAP Section 0.7.2 the no-hardcoded-
            sys_id constraint applies to flows, ACL conditions, scripts,
            seed data, UI Policies, UI Actions, Business Rules, and
            client scripts)
          * ../scripts/seed_demo_data.js (the idempotent seed script
            that calls `gs.getUserGroupID('Demo Team')` or equivalent
            GlideRecord lookup by group `name` to resolve the sys_id at
            seed time, never via hard-coded literals)
-->
<record_update table="sys_dictionary">
    <sys_dictionary action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <array>false</array>
        <attributes/>
        <audit>false</audit>
        <calculation/>
        <choice>0</choice>
        <choice_field/>
        <choice_table/>
        <column_label>Assigned Group</column_label>
        <comments>Reference to sys_user_group - the team responsible for this case. Required for Draft-&gt;Open transition (../flows/sub_flows/validate_open_transition.xml). Field-level ACL (../acl/x_[scope]_case_assigned_group_field_acl.xml) restricts write access to case_manager. Used by ACL "Assigned only" condition for case_agent role (../acl/x_[scope]_case_read_agent_assigned.xml, ../acl/x_[scope]_case_write_agent_assigned.xml). Membership of assigned_agent in assigned_group is validated by ../business_rules/x_[scope]_validate_assigned_agent_membership.xml. Replaces ArkCase CaseFile.responsibleOrganization (free-form String) with a proper foreign key to sys_user_group.</comments>
        <create_roles/>
        <default_value/>
        <defaultsort/>
        <delete_roles/>
        <dependent/>
        <dependent_on_field/>
        <display>true</display>
        <dynamic_creation>false</dynamic_creation>
        <dynamic_creation_script/>
        <dynamic_default_value/>
        <dynamic_ref_qual/>
        <element>assigned_group</element>
        <element_reference>false</element_reference>
        <foreign_database/>
        <function_definition/>
        <function_field>false</function_field>
        <internal_type>reference</internal_type>
        <mandatory>false</mandatory>
        <max_length>32</max_length>
        <name>x_[scope]_case</name>
        <next_element/>
        <primary>false</primary>
        <read_only>false</read_only>
        <read_roles/>
        <reference>sys_user_group</reference>
        <reference_cascade_rule/>
        <reference_floor/>
        <reference_key/>
        <reference_qual/>
